Euclid arm in arm with the spirit of anarchy. But many are of the highest respectability. Some are assassins. There are pale stenches and gaunt superstitions and mere shadows and lively malices: whims and amiabilities.” - Charles Fort, The Book of the Damned%0a> %0a136,137c130%0a%3c !!!%25center%25Oath%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Oath%0a140,141c133%0a%3c !!!%25center%25Curiosity%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Curiosity%0a144,145c136%0a%3c !!!%25center%25Courtiers%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Courtiers%0a148,150c139,140%0a%3c !!!%25center%25Titles%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Master (Mantle 5)'''%0a---%0a> Titles%0a> Master (Mantle 5)%0a152,153c142%0a%3c **The current Master is John Doe%0a%3c %0a---%0a> The current Master is John Doe%0a156,163c145,148%0a%3c !!!%25center%25Approaches%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Curiosity Killed The Cat and satisfaction brought it back.'''%0a%3c %0a%3c Forteans often dive into interesting situations without enough caution or what some would consider common sense, and expect to survive on their wits and expertise. Huntsmen gain a point of yearning when they bait a trap with something that sparks a courtier’s curiosity.%0a%3c %0a%3c '''It’s Never Lupus'''%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Approaches%0a> Curiosity Killed The Cat%0a> and satisfaction brought it back. Forteans often dive into interesting situations without enough caution or what some would consider common sense, and expect to survive on their wits and expertise. Huntsmen gain a point of yearning when they bait a trap with something that sparks a courtier’s curiosity.%0a> It’s Never Lupus%0a165,167c150%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!%25center%25Court Contracts%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Court Contracts%0a169d151%0a%3c %0a172c154%0a%3c [[#top | &#8593; back to top]]%0a---%0a> [&#8593; back to top]%0a
